race.description: Sthp Drill Em' Fill Em' Maiden Plate
race.comment: GRAYNITA (9) finished out of the money on debut two starts back then was beaten 3 lengths when eighth in a 1215m contest at Kyneton last start. Well placed, blinkers go on and there is no reason she cannot find winning ways. NIELSEN PARK (5) remains a maiden after four runs but was one of the favoured runners last time but could only manage to finish sixth over 1200m at Seymour. Finds a more suitable assignment this time and is a great chance to break through. SAN PUEBLO (3) missed the placings two runs back then was never in contention last start when 5 lengths away in ninth over 1100m at Moe. This more to his liking. GOOD ONYA CHAMP (4) has come through much tougher races at his two runs to date so sharp improvement would not shock.
